descript.abstract: This line data layer represents roads for Grant County, Wisconsin in 2017. [Road centerlines for Grant County, Wisconsin. Digitized from Wisconsin aerial imagery and developed for emergency mapping. Attributes are based on NENA standards and are MSAG valid where applicable.]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [This data was created specifically for use in an emergency dispatch mapping software. The attributes will be used to interpolate wireline 9-1-1 caller locations.]

attracc.attraccr: The centerline is vector data derived from Wisconsin aerial photography, Wisconsin Department of Transportation map, the Grant County MSAG, 9-1-1 Database, and individual city maps. Attribute Accuracy was tested with automated comparison to the MSAG and 9-1-1 Database as well as manual comparison to source maps.

dataqual.logic: Some of the requirements include: Lines must connect to each other at nodes. Lines must not self intersect. Tests of logical consistency were performed by ArcInfo software.
dataqual.complete: Data Completeness for the roads reflects the content of the source documents. Documents such as the MSAG and 9-1-1 Database undergo regular maintenance and this data will not reflect changes made unless regular comparisons to the MSAG and 9-1-1 Database occur.

horizpa.horizpar: Users should assess the horizontal positional accuracy with regard to the Wisconsin aerials.

vertacc.vertaccr: Users should assess the vertical positional accuracy with regard to the Wisconsin aerials.

procstep.procdesc: The centerline was digitized from the Wisconsin aerial photography at 1"=386'.
Rural street names were assigned based on the Wisconsin Department of Transportation map. Road codes were assigned based on the same map using the legend as a guide.
The rural addressing scheme was acquired from Grant County. Road ranges were attributed based on an addressing system. These ranges were verified with the MSAG (Master Street Address Guide.)

Incorporated city road names and address ranges were attributed with information obtained from individual cities. Each city was sent a map with line work created from Wisconsin aerial photography. They were asked to add street names and address ranges to the map as well as add or delete roads as required. In addition a written description of the addressing scheme was to be included.

Quality Control: Verified that roads were broken at all ESN and community boundaries. Verified line direction and checked for missing or incorrect attributes. Geocoded MSAG and 9-1-1 Database to roads file to verify MSAG valid street names and accurate address ranges.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates
